_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Embedded Software Laboratory
_source.description: Laboratory section to accompany COMPSCI 145.
_source.prerequisite_text: ( CSE 145 OR COMPSCI 145 )
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Projects in Advanced 3D Computer Graphics
_source.description: Projects in advanced 3D graphics such as illumination, geometric modeling, visualization, and animation. Topics include physically based and global illumination, solid modeling, curved surfaces, multiresolution modeling, image-based rendering, basic concepts of animation, and scientific visualization.
_source.prerequisite_text: CSE 161 AND COMPSCI 112 AND COMPSCI 161 AND COMPSCI 164 AND COMPSCI 165 AND ( CSE 45C OR I&C SCI 45C ) AND NO REPEATS ALLOWED
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Project in Operating System Organization
_source.description: Detailed specification and design of critical components of an actual operating system including a memory manager, a process server, and a file/IO subsystem. Hardware/software tradeoffs. Emphasis on logical organization of system and communication.
_source.prerequisite_text: COMPSCI 143A
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
_source.description: Techniques for efficient algorithm design, including divide-and-conquer and dynamic programming, and time/space analysis. Fast algorithms for problems applicable to networks, computer games, and scientific computing, such as sorting, shortest paths, minimum spanning trees, network flow, and pattern matching.
_source.prerequisite_text: I&C SCI 6B AND I&C SCI 6D AND ( MATH 2B OR AP CALCULUS BC ) AND ( CSE 46 OR I&C SCI 46 )
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Software Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Data Science Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Business Information Management, Computer Game Science, and Informatics majors have second right of consideration.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Computational Geometry and Geometric Modeling
_source.description: Algorithms and data structures for computational geometry and geometric modeling, with applications to game and graphics programming. Topics: convex hulls, Voronoi diagrams, algorithms for triangulation, motion planning, and data structures for geometric searching and modeling of 2D and 3D objects.
_source.prerequisite_text: I&C SCI 46 or CSE 46. I&C SCI 46 with a grade of C or better. CSE 46 with a grade of C or better
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Machine Learning and Data-Mining
_source.description: Introduction to principles of machine learning and data-mining applied to real-world datasets. Typical applications include spam filtering, object recognition, and credit scoring.

_source.prerequisite_text: I&C SCI 6B AND I&C SCI 6D AND ( MATH 2B OR AP CALCULUS BC ) AND ( MATH 3A OR I&C SCI 6N ) AND ( STATS 67 OR ( STATS 120A AND ( STATS 7 OR AP STATISTICS ) ) )
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Special Topics in Information and Computer Science
_source.description: Studies in selected areas of Information and Computer Science. Topics addressed vary each quarter.
_source.prerequisite_text: I&C SCI 51 AND ( CSE 46 OR I&C SCI 46 ) AND ( EECS 116 OR COMPSCI 122A )
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Computer Simulation
_source.description: Discrete event-driven simulation; continuous system simulation; basic probability as pertaining to input distributions and output analysis; stochastic and deterministic simulation; static and dynamic system simulation.
_source.prerequisite_text: I&C SCI 51 AND I&C SCI 6B AND IN4MATX 43 AND ( MATH 3A OR I&C SCI 6N ) AND ( STATS 67 OR ( STATS 120A AND ( STATS 7 OR AP STATISTICS ) ) ) AND NO REPEATS ALLOWED
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Applications of Probability in Computer Science
_source.description: Application of probability to real-world problems in computer science. Typical topics include analysis of algorithms and graphs, probabilistic language models, network traffic modeling, data compression, and reliability modeling.
_source.prerequisite_text: STATS 67 AND I&C SCI 6B AND I&C SCI 6D AND ( MATH 2B OR AP CALCULUS BC ) AND ( MATH 3A OR I&C SCI 6N ) AND NO REPEATS ALLOWED
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Introduction to Computational Biology
_source.description: The use of theories and methods based on computer science, mathematics, and physics in molecular biology and biochemistry. Basics in biomolecular modeling. Analysis of sequence and structural data of biomolecules. Analysis of biomolecular functions.
_source.prerequisite_text: MATH 2D or MATH 3A or STATS 7 or STATS 8

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Formal Languages and Automata
_source.description: Formal aspects of describing and recognizing languages by grammars and automata.  Parsing regular and context-free languages. Ambiguity, nondeterminism. Elements of computability; Turning machines, random access machines, undecidable problems, NP-completeness.
_source.prerequisite_text: I&C SCI 6B AND I&C SCI 6D AND ( MATH 2B OR AP CALCULUS BC ) AND ( CSE 46 OR I&C SCI 46 )
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Cognitive Sciences Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Language Science Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Quantum Computation and Information
_source.description: Basic models for quantum computation and their foundations in quantum mechanics. Quantum complexity classes and quantum algorithms, including algorithms for factoring and quantum simulation. Introduction to quantum information theory and quantum entanglement.
_source.prerequisite_text: (I&C SCI 6N or MATH 3A) and COMPSCI 161
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Language Processor Construction
_source.description: Project course which provides working laboratory experience in construction and behavior of compilers and interpreters. Students build actual language processors and perform experiments which reveal their behaviors.
_source.prerequisite_text: COMPSCI 142A or CSE 142
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Principles of Operating Systems
_source.description: Principles and concepts of process and resource management, especially as seen in operating systems. Processes, memory management, protection, scheduling, file systems, and I/O systems are covered. Concepts illustrated in the context of several well-known systems.
_source.prerequisite_text: (I&C SCI 46 or CSE 46) and (I&C SCI 51 or EECS 31 or CSE 31)
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Programming in Multitasking Operating Systems
_source.description: User- and systems-level programming of modern Internet-connected, multi-user, multitasking operating systems. Shells, scripting, filters, pipelines, programmability, extensibility, concurrency, inter-process communication. Concrete examples of a modern operating system (such as, but not necessarily, Unix programmed in C) are used.
_source.prerequisite_text: I&C SCI 51 AND COMPSCI 143A AND ( CSE 46 OR I&C SCI 46 ) AND NO REPEATS ALLOWED
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Neural Networks and Deep Learning
_source.description: Neural network and deep learning from multiple perspectives. Theory of parallel distributed processing systems, algorithmic approaches for learning from data in various manners, applications to difficult problems in AI from computer vision, to natural language understanding, to bioinformatics and chemoinformatics.
_source.prerequisite_text: (STATS 120A and STATS 120B) or MATH 121A or COMPSCI 178 or COMPSCI 273A
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Algorithms for Probabilistic and Deterministic Graphical Models
_source.description: Graphical model techniques dealing with probabilistic and deterministic knowledge representations. Focuses on graphical models such as constraint networks, Bayesian networks, and Markov networks that have become a central paradigm for knowledge representation and reasoning in AI and general computer science.
_source.prerequisite_text: COMPSCI 171
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Computational Systems Biology
_source.description: Computational inference and modeling of gene regulation networks, signal transduction pathways, and the effects of regulatory networks in cellular processes, development, and disease. Introduction of required mathematical, computational, and data handling tools.
_source.prerequisite_text: COMPSCI 184A
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Artificial Intelligence Frontiers: Technical, Ethical, and Societal
_source.description: Explores the frontiers of artificial intelligence and related technologies with a focus on the underlying ethical, legal, and societal challenges and opportunities they create. Encourages critical thinking about these issues.
_source.prerequisite_text: COMPSCI 171 and COMPSCI 172B. Recommended: COMPSCI 178
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.

_source.school: Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
_source.title: Digital Image Processing
_source.description: Introduction to the fundamental concepts of digital signal and image processing as applicable in areas such as multimedia, graphics, AI, data mining, databases, vision, or video games. Topics include image representation, space- and frequency-domain transformations, filters, segmentation, and compression.
_source.prerequisite_text: (I&C SCI 46 or CSE 46) and I&C SCI 6D and (MATH 3A or I&C SCI 6N). I&C SCI 46 with a grade of C or better. CSE 46 with a grade of C or better. I&C SCI 6D with a grade of C or better. MATH 3A with a grade of C or better. I&C SCI 6N with a grade of C or better
_source.restriction: School of Info & Computer Sci students have first consideration for enrollment. Computer Science Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.
